#MEM id=supabase-rls source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/raj/skills/custom/supabase-rls/SKILL.md savings=5%
M||tx|---
M||name|sb-rls
M||desc|Row Level sec behavioral guide for rj. Every table that stores vt or us data must have RLS enabled. Covers policy patterns, vt-scoping, service role rules, and the pre-sc-change checklist.
M||vers|1.0.0
M||tx|---
M|Purp|tx|yv is a multi-vt sy (nz + hb). w/o RLS, a bug in the vt-switching logic cld expose nz's data to hb's context — or vice versa. RLS is the last line of defence after application-level scoping. It must be on every data table.
M|Purp|**Ha|** No table ships w/o an explicit RLS decision documented. "We'll add it later" is not acceptable — sc changes are expensive and RLS retrofits require auditing every existing row.
M|Purp|tx|---
M|Vent|tx|```sql
M|Vent|tx|-- Enable RLS
M|Vent|tx|ALTER TABLE analytics_events ENABLE ROW LEVEL sec;
M|Vent|-- R|only the active vt's rows
M|Vent|tx|cr POLICY "venture_read" ON analytics_events
M|Vent|tx|FOR SELECT
M|Vent|tx|USING (venture_slug = current_setting('app.venture_slug', true));
M|Vent|-- I|only insert into active vt
M|Vent|tx|cr POLICY "venture_insert" ON analytics_events
M|Vent|tx|FOR INSERT
M|Vent|tx|w/ CHECK (venture_slug = current_setting('app.venture_slug', true));
M|Vent|tx|```
M|Auth|tx|```sql
M|Auth|tx|ALTER TABLE user_preferences ENABLE ROW LEVEL sec;
M|Auth|tx|cr POLICY "auth_read" ON user_preferences
M|Auth|tx|FOR SELECT
M|Auth|tx|USING (auth.uid() = user_id);
M|Auth|tx|cr POLICY "auth_write" ON user_preferences
M|Auth|tx|FOR ALL
M|Auth|tx|USING (auth.uid() = user_id)
M|Auth|tx|w/ CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);
M|Auth|tx|```
M|Comb|tx|```sql
M|Comb|tx|cr POLICY "venture_auth_read" ON cg
M|Comb|tx|FOR SELECT
M|Comb|tx|USING (
M|Comb|tx|venture_slug = current_setting('app.venture_slug', true)
M|Comb|tx|AND auth.uid() = owner_id
M|Comb|tx|);
M|Comb|tx|```
M|Serv|tx|```sql
M|Serv|tx|-- Service role bypasses RLS by default in sb
M|Serv|tx|-- Use ONLY in server-side cron rt w/ CRON_SECRET validation
M|Serv|tx|-- NEVER use service role key from client cp
M|Serv|tx|```
M|Serv|tx|---
M|Sett|tx|```ts
M|Sett|tx|// At the start of any rt that uses vt-scoped tables
M|Sett|tx|await sb.rpc('set_config', {
M|Sett|sett|'app.venture_slug',
M|Sett|valu|ventureSlug,
M|Sett|is_l|true
M|Sett|tx|})
M|Sett|tx|// Now all queries on this connection respect the RLS policy
M|Sett|tx|```
M|Sett|tx|---
M|Serv|tx|\| Situation \| Key to use \|
M|Serv|tx|\|-----------\|-----------\|
M|Serv|tx|\| Server-side ap rt (normal) \| Anon key + us auth sn \|
M|Serv|tx|\| Cron jobs (admin operations) \| Service role key — bypasses RLS by ds \|
M|Serv|tx|\| Client cp \| NEVER use service role key \|
M|Serv|tx|\| sb storage (file uploads) \| Anon key w/ storage policies \|
M|Serv|**Ha|** `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` appears ONLY in rt that have been validated w/ `CRON_SECRET` header, or in explicit admin-only endpoints. Never in `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.
M|Serv|tx|---
M|Pre-|Befo|
M|Pre-|it|[ ] RLS enabled on this table? (`ALTER TABLE ... ENABLE ROW LEVEL sec`)
M|Pre-|- [ |uses `auth.uid()` or `venture_slug` scoping — not open to all?
M|Pre-|- [ |prevents cross-vt writes? (`w/ CHECK` clause present)
M|Pre-|- [ |same scoping as SELECT?
M|Pre-|- [ |shd regular us be able to dl? Who can?
M|Pre-|- [ |are any operations on this table intended to bypass RLS? Is that documented and intentional?
M|Pre-|it|[ ] Has dv reviewed and approved this sc change?
M|Pre-|it|[ ] Is this change logged in MEMORY.md w/ its rationale?
M|Pre-|tx|---
M|Test|Befo|
M|Test|tx|```bash
M|In S|tx|SET ROLE anon;
M|In S|tx|SELECT * FROM cg;  -- shd return 0 rows or er
M|Test|tx|SELECT set_config('app.venture_slug', 'wrong-vt', true);
M|Test|tx|SELECT * FROM cg;  -- shd return 0 rows
M|Test|tx|SELECT set_config('app.venture_slug', 'nz', true);
M|Test|tx|SELECT * FROM cg;  -- shd return nz rows only
M|Test|tx|```
M|Test|tx|---
M|Comm|tx|\| Mistake \| Consequence \| Fix \|
M|Comm|tx|\|---------\|------------\|-----\|
M|Comm|tx|\| `FOR ALL USING (true)` \| Open to everyone \| Scope w/ auth.uid() or venture_slug \|
M|Comm|tx|\| No INSERT policy \| Anyone can write \| Add w/ CHECK clause \|
M|Comm|tx|\| Relying only on app-level filtering \| Bug in app = data leak \| RLS is the safety net, not the app filter \|
M|Comm|tx|\| Using service role in client \| Bypasses RLS everywhere \| Service role server-side only \|
M|Comm|tx|\| Forgetting to set `app.venture_slug` \| RLS policy returns no rows \| Set config at rt start \|